  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 800967,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "The web application allowed users to upload SVG files via chat.line.biz without properly filtering or disabling scripts embedded inside the SVG content. As a result, an attacker could upload a malicious SVG containing JavaScript, and when another user later opened this file in the management interface, the embedded script would be executed in the browser, leading to a stored cross-site scripting (Stored XSS) vulnerability.",
